  "prompt": "Why do some emails end in \".edu\"?",
  "response": "Emails that end in \".edu\" are typically associated with educational institutions. The \".edu\" domain is a top-level domain (TLD) used exclusively by accredited postsecondary institutions in the United States. These include universities, colleges, community colleges, and other educational entities. The .edu TLD is reserved for these institutions to help identify and authenticate educational organizations, providing a clear indication that the email address belongs to someone affiliated with a recognized school or university. If you see an email ending in \".edu,\" it is likely being used by a student, faculty member, or administrator associated with the institution.",
